Total Quality Management (TQM) is a philosophy of management for continuously improving the quality of goods, services and processes. TQM is a combination of quality and management tools that aim to increase benefits and reduce losses due to wasteful practices. This course will present the various TQM concepts, frameworks, and principles that form a foundation for implementing the quality culture. The course also gives an overview on widely implemented quality standards. During the course various quality improvement tools and techniques are explained and compared. The course will provide the participants with the understanding of the arrangement of TQM on the example of various organizations in order to demonstrate how to implement TQM in practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course will provide with the the overview of Total Quality Management (TQM) approaches, frameworks, underlying principles, standards, tools and techniques with emphasis on both theory and practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, students are able
to:
Comprehend the TQM theory, frameworks and principles.
Understand the essence of quality standards (ISO9000, ISO14000, OHSAS, SA8000 etc.).
Realize TQM arrangement in the organization.
Distinguish between various TQM tools and techniques (e.g. CI/Kaizen, FMEA, 5S, Six Sigma, Pareto charts, Fishbone/Ishikawa Diagrams etc.).
